1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
What if practicing different skills together could supercharge your learning?

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,400
This method is called interleaving practice.

3
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:11,200
Unlike blocked practice, where you repeat one skill, interleaving mixes them up.

4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:14,800
Research shows that interleaving can improve retention and problem-solving.

5
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:15,600
But why?

6
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:21,200
Cognitive studies suggest that switching tasks forces your brain to make connections, enhancing understanding.

7
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:24,800
So, next time you study, try mixing it up!

8
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:28,400
You’ll not only learn better, but you'll remember longer.

9
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,400
Want to boost your learning?

10
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:31,600
Start interleaving today!

11
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,600
Follow for more science-backed tips.
